1) Interpret interest rates as required rates of return, discount rates, or opportunity costs
2) Explain an interest rate as the sum of a real risk-free rate and premiums that compensate investor for bearing distinct types of risk
3) Calculate and interpret the future value and the present value of a single sum of money, an ordinary annuity, an annuity due, a perpetuity, and a series of unequal cash flows
4) Demonstrate the use of a time line in modelling and solving time value of money problems
5) Calculate the solution for time value of money problems with different frequencies of compounding
6) Calculate and interpret the effective annual rate, given the stated annual interest rate and the frequency of compounding
